[[tab Personnel File]]

/> Welcome to the SCP Foundation personnel database. Please enter access credentials.

[[collapsible show="[PLEASE INPUT CREDENTIALS]" hide="Username: ******* Password: *********"]]


Identity confirmed. Welcome, 

[[module ListUsers users="."]]
**%%title%%**.
[[/module]]

**[ACCESSING FILE...COMPLETE]**


**Name:** Lucius Elijah Veritas

**Security Clearance:** 4

**Current Assignment:** Director of Research (SCP-914).

**Position:** Head of Experimental Security. 

**Former Position:** Humanoid Psychology.

**Current Location:** Site-19-23.

**Serial Number:** 3475-83537

**Profile:** Specialised in personnel/humanoid interaction and Experimental Security, Veritas' primary position is the Director of Research overseeing and mandating testing on [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-914 |SCP-914]]].

While he started working with humanoid objects, the overseeing of tests involving SCP-914 has been his full-time job for several years. During these years, his management has been described from ''strict, but fair'' to ''despotic and dictatorial''. 

Since testing with SCP-914 is considered to be a ''test of professional skill'' by a portion of new researchers, Dr. Veritas currently holds the record of ''termination of most personnel outside of O5 command'', with 132. 

> **FROM:** Dr. Daniels, Junior Researcher, Site 19
> **TO:** Dr. Gears, [REDACTED]
> **SUBJECT:** Testing with 914
> 
> Gears, can you get Veritas off my back? I promise to be careful this time, I even read and signed his stupid [[[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-914-experiment-log-guidelines |security manual for 914]]] three times!
> 
> ~ Junior Researcher Daniels.

> **FROM:** Dr. Gears, [REDACTED]
> **TO:** Dr. Daniels, Junior Researcher, Site 19
> **SUBJECT:** RE: Testing with 914
> 
> Dear Dr. Daniels,
> 
> According to the testing logs from two weeks ago, you attempted to 'refine' a flamethrower, which resulted in considerable damage to SCP-914's containment chamber and SCP-914 itself. The repairs are still being made at the time of writing. I was not present at the time of testing, but at least two researchers described the result as, and I quote: ''Something you would see in a Terminator movie''. While I am not familiar with the particular film, Dr. Julie is still in therapy following the incident. I feel forced to side with Dr. Veritas on this one.
> 
> ~ Dr. Gears.

